- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new extension to the adversarial training framework for generative models, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed architecture involves multiple generators working together to represent a target distribution, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence research.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The authors demonstrate the feasibility of their approach on the MNIST dataset, which is a well-known computer vision benchmark.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The proposed architecture involves training multiple neural networks to work together, which is a topic within neural computing.
- cs.SD (Sound): There is no direct mention of sound in the paper, but this category is included as a catch-all for any potential applications of the proposed approach to sound-related tasks.
